==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Singsong
<hw>Sing"song`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Bad
singing or poetry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A drawling or monotonous tone, as of a badly
executed song.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Singsong</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Singsong
<hw>Sing"song`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Drawling; monotonous; having a
monotonous cadence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Singsong</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Singsong
<hw>Sing"song`</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To write poor poetry.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

